# Buying Decision Factors

**What drives software purchasing decisions**

| Decision Factor | Enterprise | Mid-Market | Small Business | Overall Weight |
|-----------------|------------|------------|----------------|----------------|
| **Security & Compliance** | 92% | 78% | 45% | 8.5/10 |
| **Integration Capabilities** | 89% | 85% | 62% | 8.2/10 |
| **Scalability** | 86% | 91% | 58% | 7.9/10 |
| **Total Cost of Ownership** | 71% | 88% | 94% | 7.7/10 |
| **Ease of Implementation** | 68% | 82% | 89% | 7.4/10 |
| **Vendor Reputation** | 83% | 69% | 51% | 7.1/10 |
| **Customer Support** | 75% | 79% | 76% | 7.0/10 |

::: warning
**Critical Gap:** 73% struggle with vendor lock-in concerns
:::

@notes:
- Security dominates enterprise decision criteria
- Cost considerations vary significantly by segment
- Integration capabilities universally important
- Vendor lock-in creates market opportunity

