# Implementation Success Factors

**What determines successful software deployments**

| Success Factor | Impact Score | Frequency | Control Level |
|----------------|--------------|-----------|---------------|
| **Executive Sponsorship** | 9.2/10 | 78% | Customer |
| **Change Management** | 8.8/10 | 65% | Shared |
| **User Training Quality** | 8.5/10 | 82% | Vendor |
| **Technical Architecture** | 8.3/10 | 91% | Vendor |
| **Project Management** | 8.1/10 | 89% | Shared |
| **Data Migration Planning** | 7.9/10 | 73% | Shared |
| **Phased Rollout Strategy** | 7.6/10 | 67% | Shared |

::: warning
**Risk Factor:** 42% of implementations lack adequate change management
:::

@notes:
- Executive sponsorship critical but inconsistent
- Change management often overlooked but high impact
- Vendor-controlled factors generally well-executed
- Implementation success requires shared responsibility

